<seg id=1> Insurance Monitoring Begins in Beijing </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Beijing, Jan. 21: A project assisting The People's Bank of China in its monitoring of rules and regulations drafted by foreign-invested insurance institutions in China, and a research project investigating insurance standardization of systems and measures, began in Beijing a few days ago. </seg>
<seg id=3> This project will be funded by the Royal & Sun Alliance Insurance Group of England and Lincoln National Group of the United States, while the actual monitoring will be performed by the accountancy firm of PricewaterhouseCoopers. Total investment in the project will be 1.4 million U.S. dollars. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> This insurance monitoring project will involve both a systematic analysis of foreign-invested insurance practices in China and existing laws and regulations for insurance monitoring. It will work as a means of drawing upon the advanced experienced of foreign monitors in order to benefit the development of insurance monitoring in China and to perfect a constructive research proposal for laws and regulations for monitoring. </seg>
<seg id=5> The project will be a further investigation into the existing fundamental laws and regulations concerning the People's Bank of China's monitoring of foreign-invested insurance organizations. Efforts will be concentrated upon strengthening management of organization and operations, especially in developing an early-warning system. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> According to reports, new regulations will perfect the monitoring system for foreign-invested insurance organizations currently in China's market, and at the same time assist the People's Bank of China in strengthening the monitoring system for the whole insurance market. </seg>
</p>
